{"cursor":"4265","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n{{Infobox River\n  | river_name = Segura map = LocalizaciÃ³n del rÃ­o Segura.png image_name =\n  | SeguraWK.jpg caption = Source of the Segura River origin = Fuente Segura,\n  | JaÃ©n mouth = Guardamar del Segura, Alicante basin_countries = Spain length =\n  | 325 km elevation = 1,413 m mouth_elevation = 0 m discharge = Cieza: 26.3\n  | mÂ³/s watershed = 19,525 kmÂ²\n}}\n\n\n\n)]]\n\n\n\n'Segura' (, ; Latin: Thader, Arabic: War-Alabiat) is a medium-sized river in\nsoutheastern Spain.\n\nIt starts at Santiago Pontones (province of JaÃ©n), passes Calasparra, Cieza,\nMurcia, BeniajÃ¡n, Orihuela, Rojales and ends in the Mediterranean Sea near\nGuardamar del Segura in the province of Alicante. Some of its tributaries are\nthe Mundo (which starts near RiÃ³par), the AlhÃ¡rabe (which starts in Moratalla),\nthe Mula and the GuadalentÃ­n.\n\nThe Segura is usually in a state of semi-permanent drought, however, now and\nthen, it does occasionally flood as the consequence of the torrential rains\nwhich typically take place once every 6â9 years approximately, always in Autumn.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=\"center\"\n|+ 'Avg. discharge'\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n! Place !! Discharge\n|- Cenajo || align=\"right\" |17,1 mÂ³/s - Cieza || align=\"right\" |26,3 mÂ³/s -\n|Orihuela || align=\"right\" |5 mÂ³/s - Guardamar del Segura || align=\"right\"\n||1 mÂ³/s }\n\nIn the twentieth century significant flooding occurred in 1946, 1948, 1973,\n1982, 1987 and 1989. Since 1990 the lower reaches of the river have been\ncanalized, removing meanders and hence improving the evacuation of flood waters.\nThe new canal was put to the test in September 1997 and October 2000 when heavy\nrainfall resulted in significant runoff.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" align=\"center\"\n|+ 'Segura floods in Murcia and Orihuela'\n|- style=\"background:#efefef;\"\n! Date !! Murcia!! Orihuela\n|- October, 1651 || align=\"right\" |1.700 mÂ³/s || - October, 1834 ||\n|align=\"right\" |1.000 mÂ³/s || - October, 1879 || align=\"right\" |1.890 mÂ³/s ||\n|align=\"right\" |2.000 mÂ³/s - April, 1946 || align=\"right\" |1.187 mÂ³/s ||\n|align=\"right\" |1.138 mÂ³/s - October, 1948 || align=\"right\" |934 mÂ³/s ||\n|align=\"right\" |1.172 mÂ³/s - November, 1987 || || align=\"right\" |1.000 mÂ³/s }\n\nThe alluvial plain is called the Vega del Segura and is a very productive\nagricultural region growing a wide variety of fruit, vegetables and flowers.\nThe Vegas are divided into three areas: Alta, Media and Baja (upper, medium,\nand lower).\n\nThe Segura is one of the most polluted rivers in Europe. However, in recent\nyears extensive water management techniques and the implementation of waste\nwater treatment plants have greatly improved the situation.  What must be considered is that the mean discharge is\naround 2 to 3 mÂ³/s in Murcia city making it very difficult to dilute illegal\npollutants.\n","linknr":163,"url":"segura","recorded":1364119351,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Segura&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Segura&action=edit","//en.wikipedia.org/apple-touch-icon.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.wikihiero%7Cmediawiki.legacy.commonPrint%2Cshared%7Cmw.PopUpMediaTransform%7Cskins.vector&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=site&only=styles&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=startup&only=scripts&skin=vector&*","//bits.wikimedia.org/geoiplookup","//meta.wikimedia.org","#mw-head","#p-search","/wiki/Segura_(disambiguation)","/wiki/File:SeguraWK.jpg","//upload.wik